# Taskmaster project context

This is a **pnpm monorepo** (Node 20+). Do not assume npm/yarn unless the user asks.

## Layout

| Package | Path | Role |
|---------|------|------|
| `@taskmaster/web` | `apps/web/` | Next.js 15 App Router UI, REST API routes under `src/app/api/` |
| `@taskmaster/core` | `packages/core/` | File-backed task storage, Zod schemas, shared domain logic |
| `@taskmaster/mcp` | `packages/mcp/` | MCP server for Cursor agents (`@modelcontextprotocol/sdk`) |

## Stack

- **Web**: Next.js 15, React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4 (`@tailwindcss/postcss`)
- **Agents**: `@cursor/sdk` for optional "Run agent" — not Vercel AI SDK
- **Data**: `.taskmaster/` JSON + NDJSON work logs in the user's project repo (not this repo's DB)

## Commands

- `pnpm install` / `pnpm build` / `pnpm dev` — from repo root
- `pnpm mcp` — run MCP server (set `TASKMASTER_PROJECT` to target repo)
- `pnpm typecheck` — typecheck all packages

## Imported rules

Rules under `.cursor/rules/*/` come from [awesome-cursorrules](https://github.com/PatrickJS/awesome-cursorrules). Prefer this file and existing code when they conflict with generic Next.js or UI-library rules (e.g. shadcn, Vercel AI SDK, DaisyUI).

## Scope when editing

- UI and API routes: `apps/web/**`
- Shared task logic: `packages/core/**`
- MCP tools: `packages/mcp/**`
